    Title: Il Convito
    Location: II xiv 11
By: Dante
Tags:
  - Beauty-Peace=Beauty=Music
  - 532
---
Music draws to itself the human spirits (senses), which are principally vapours
of the heart, as it were, so that they almost cease to act; so entirely is the
soul one thing when it listens, and the power of all (the rest of the senses)
seems to fly to that sensible spirit which receives sound.
